The verifier exhausts all sorted positive sextuples through level fourteen.
For each sextuple it computes all 64 subset invariant multiplicities by exact
integer fusion DP, checks T<=N+P, enumerates every even support-disjoint sign
assignment, and independently checks both the full subset contraction and the
half-integral identity.  This is a bounded cross-check of Proposition 25D4;
the proof is the unbounded case analysis in CENTRAL_CHARACTER_Q3_SEARCH.md.
